pfMIBObjects.name: pfMIBObjects

revisions.description: Add separate counter for failed 'route-to' applications
Add pf(4) table byte/packet counters for 'match' rules
Add separate counter for failed translations

pfMIBObjects.contactinfo: Author: Joel Knight email: knight.joel@gmail.com www: http://www.packetmischief.ca/openbsd-snmp-mibs/
pfMIBObjects.description: The MIB module for gathering information from OpenBSD's packet filter.

pfRunning.name: pfRunning
pfRunning.description: Indicates whether pf is enabled or not.

pfRuntime.name: pfRuntime
pfRuntime.description: Indicates how long pf has been enabled. If pf is not enabled, indicates how long pf has been disabled. If pf has not been explicitly enabled or disabled since the system was booted, the value will be 0.

pfDebug.name: pfDebug
pfDebug.description: Indicates the debug level that pf is running at.

pfHostid.name: pfHostid
pfHostid.description: The (unique) host id of the machine running pf.

pfCntMatch.name: pfCntMatch
pfCntMatch.description: The number of packets that have matched a filter rule.

pfCntBadOffset.name: pfCntBadOffset
pfCntBadOffset.description: The number of packets that have had a bad offset value.

pfCntShort.name: pfCntShort
pfCntShort.description: The number of packets that were too short to contain a valid header.

pfCntNormalize.name: pfCntNormalize
pfCntNormalize.description: The number of packets that were normalized using the packet scrubber.

pfCntMemory.name: pfCntMemory
pfCntMemory.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to memory limitations.

pfCntTimestamp.name: pfCntTimestamp
pfCntTimestamp.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to improper RFC1323 timestamp.

pfCntCongestion.name: pfCntCongestion
pfCntCongestion.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to congestion on the interface.

pfCntIpOption.name: pfCntIpOption
pfCntIpOption.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to having options set in the IP header.

pfCntProtoCksum.name: pfCntProtoCksum
pfCntProtoCksum.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to memory limitations.

pfCntStateMismatch.name: pfCntStateMismatch
pfCntStateMismatch.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to a state table mismatch.

pfCntStateInsert.name: pfCntStateInsert
pfCntStateInsert.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to errors creating a state table entry.

pfCntStateLimit.name: pfCntStateLimit
pfCntStateLimit.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to the per-rule max state limit being reached.

pfCntSrcLimit.name: pfCntSrcLimit
pfCntSrcLimit.description: The number of packets that were dropped due to stateful connection tracking. A packet could be dropped due to resource limits (memory) or due to a tracking limit being reached.

pfCntSynproxy.name: pfCntSynproxy
pfCntSynproxy.description: The number of packets that were dropped during the TCP synproxy process.

pfCntTranslate.name: pfCntTranslate
pfCntTranslate.description: The number of packets that were dropped because network address translation was requested and no unused port was available.

pfCntNoRoute.name: pfCntNoRoute
pfCntNoRoute.description: The number of packets that were dropped because policy based routing was requested but no target addresses were available.

pfStateCount.name: pfStateCount
pfStateCount.description: The number of entries in the state table.

pfStateSearches.name: pfStateSearches
pfStateSearches.description: The number of searches against the state table.

pfStateInserts.name: pfStateInserts
pfStateInserts.description: The number of inserts into the state table.

pfStateRemovals.name: pfStateRemovals
pfStateRemovals.description: The number of removals from the state table.

pfLogIfName.name: pfLogIfName
pfLogIfName.description: The name of the interface configured using 'set loginterface'. If no interface has been configured, the object will be empty.

pfLogIfIpBytesIn.name: pfLogIfIpBytesIn
pfLogIfIpBytesIn.description: The number of IPv4 bytes passed in on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIpBytesOut.name: pfLogIfIpBytesOut
pfLogIfIpBytesOut.description: The number of IPv4 bytes passed out on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIpPktsInPass.name: pfLogIfIpPktsInPass
pfLogIfIpPktsInPass.description: The number of IPv4 packets passed in on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIpPktsInDrop.name: pfLogIfIpPktsInDrop
pfLogIfIpPktsInDrop.description: The number of dropped IPv4 packets coming in on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIpPktsOutPass.name: pfLogIfIpPktsOutPass
pfLogIfIpPktsOutPass.description: The number of IPv4 packets passed out on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIpPktsOutDrop.name: pfLogIfIpPktsOutDrop
pfLogIfIpPktsOutDrop.description: The number of dropped IPv4 packets going out on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIp6BytesIn.name: pfLogIfIp6BytesIn
pfLogIfIp6BytesIn.description: The number of IPv6 bytes passed in on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIp6BytesOut.name: pfLogIfIp6BytesOut
pfLogIfIp6BytesOut.description: The number of IPv6 bytes passed out on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIp6PktsInPass.name: pfLogIfIp6PktsInPass
pfLogIfIp6PktsInPass.description: The number of IPv6 packets passed in on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIp6PktsInDrop.name: pfLogIfIp6PktsInDrop
pfLogIfIp6PktsInDrop.description: The number of dropped IPv6 packets coming in on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIp6PktsOutPass.name: pfLogIfIp6PktsOutPass
pfLogIfIp6PktsOutPass.description: The number of IPv6 packets passed out on the loginterface.

pfLogIfIp6PktsOutDrop.name: pfLogIfIp6PktsOutDrop
pfLogIfIp6PktsOutDrop.description: The number of dropped IPv6 packets going out on the loginterface.

pfSrcTrackCount.name: pfSrcTrackCount
pfSrcTrackCount.description: The number of entries in the source tracking table.

pfSrcTrackSearches.name: pfSrcTrackSearches
pfSrcTrackSearches.description: The number of searches against the source tracking table.

pfSrcTrackInserts.name: pfSrcTrackInserts
pfSrcTrackInserts.description: The number of inserts into the source tracking table.

pfSrcTrackRemovals.name: pfSrcTrackRemovals
pfSrcTrackRemovals.description: The number of removals from the source tracking table.

pfLimitStates.name: pfLimitStates
pfLimitStates.description: The maximum number of entries in the memory pool used by state table entries (filter rules that specify 'keep state').

pfLimitSourceNodes.name: pfLimitSourceNodes
pfLimitSourceNodes.description: The maximum number of entries in the memory pool used for tracking source IP addresses (filter rules that specify 'sticky-address' or 'source-track' options).

pfLimitFragments.name: pfLimitFragments
pfLimitFragments.description: The maximum number of entries in the memory pool used for packet reassembly (scrub rules).

pfLimitMaxTables.name: pfLimitMaxTables
pfLimitMaxTables.description: The maximum number of tables that can be created as part of the active ruleset.

pfLimitMaxTableEntries.name: pfLimitMaxTableEntries
pfLimitMaxTableEntries.description: The overall maximum number of addresses that can be stored in tables.

pfTimeoutTcpFirst.name: pfTimeoutTcpFirst
pfTimeoutTcpFirst.description: State after receiving the first TCP packet in a new connection.

pfTimeoutTcpOpening.name: pfTimeoutTcpOpening
pfTimeoutTcpOpening.description: State before the destination host ever sends a packet in response to a new connection from this host.

pfTimeoutTcpEstablished.name: pfTimeoutTcpEstablished
pfTimeoutTcpEstablished.description: State when a TCP connection is fully established.

pfTimeoutTcpClosing.name: pfTimeoutTcpClosing
pfTimeoutTcpClosing.description: State after the first FIN has been sent.

pfTimeoutTcpFinWait.name: pfTimeoutTcpFinWait
pfTimeoutTcpFinWait.description: State after both FINs are sent and the connection is closed.

pfTimeoutTcpClosed.name: pfTimeoutTcpClosed
pfTimeoutTcpClosed.description: State after the first RST has been sent.

pfTimeoutUdpFirst.name: pfTimeoutUdpFirst
pfTimeoutUdpFirst.description: State after receiving the first UDP packet.

pfTimeoutUdpSingle.name: pfTimeoutUdpSingle
pfTimeoutUdpSingle.description: State if the source sends more than 1 packet but the destination has never sent a packet back.

pfTimeoutUdpMultiple.name: pfTimeoutUdpMultiple
pfTimeoutUdpMultiple.description: State when both hosts have sent packets.

pfTimeoutIcmpFirst.name: pfTimeoutIcmpFirst
pfTimeoutIcmpFirst.description: State after receiving the first ICMP packet.

pfTimeoutIcmpError.name: pfTimeoutIcmpError
pfTimeoutIcmpError.description: State when an ICMP error comes back in response to an ICMP packet.

pfTimeoutOtherFirst.name: pfTimeoutOtherFirst
pfTimeoutOtherFirst.description: State after receiving the first packet.

pfTimeoutOtherSingle.name: pfTimeoutOtherSingle
pfTimeoutOtherSingle.description: State if the source sends more than 1 packet but the destination has never sent a packet back.

pfTimeoutOtherMultiple.name: pfTimeoutOtherMultiple
pfTimeoutOtherMultiple.description: State when both hosts have sent packets.

pfTimeoutFragment.name: pfTimeoutFragment
pfTimeoutFragment.description: How long before an unassembled fragment is expired.

pfTimeoutInterval.name: pfTimeoutInterval
pfTimeoutInterval.description: Interval before purging expired states and fragments.

pfTimeoutAdaptiveStart.name: pfTimeoutAdaptiveStart
pfTimeoutAdaptiveStart.description: When the number of state entries exceeds this value, adaptive scaling begins.

pfTimeoutAdaptiveEnd.name: pfTimeoutAdaptiveEnd
pfTimeoutAdaptiveEnd.description: When reaching this number of state entries, all timeout values become zero, effectively purging all state entries immediately.

pfTimeoutSrcTrack.name: pfTimeoutSrcTrack
pfTimeoutSrcTrack.description: Time that a source tracking entry will stay around after the last state expires.

pfIfNumber.name: pfIfNumber
pfIfNumber.description: The number of network interfaces present on this system.

pfIfTable.name: pfIfTable
pfIfTable.description: A list of individual interfaces. The number of entries is given by the value of pfIfNumber.

pfIfEntry.name: pfIfEntry
pfIfEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

pfIfIndex.name: pfIfIndex
pfIfIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

pfIfType.name: pfIfType
pfIfType.description: Denotes whether the interface is a group interface, an interface instance, or whether it's been removed or destroyed.

pfIfRefs.name: pfIfRefs
pfIfRefs.description: The number of state and/or source track entries which reference the interface.

pfIfRules.name: pfIfRules
pfIfRules.description: The number of rules which reference the interface.

pfIfIn4PassPkts.name: pfIfIn4PassPkts
pfIfIn4PassPkts.description: The number of IPv4 packets passed in.

pfIfIn4PassBytes.name: pfIfIn4PassBytes

pfIfOut4BlockPkts.description: The number of outgoing IPv4 bytes blocked.

pfIfOut4BlockBytes.name: pfIfOut4BlockBytes

pfIfOut6PassBytes.description: The number of IPv6 bytes passed out.

pfIfOut6BlockPkts.description: The number of outgoing IPv6 bytes blocked.

pfTblNumber.name: pfTblNumber
pfTblNumber.description: The number of tables present on this system.

pfTblTable.name: pfTblTable
pfTblTable.description: A list of individual tables. The number of entries is given by the value of tblNumber.

pfTblEntry.name: pfTblEntry
pfTblEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular table.

pfTblIndex.name: pfTblIndex
pfTblIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each table.

pfTblAddresses.name: pfTblAddresses
pfTblAddresses.description: The number of addresses currently stored in the table.

pfTblAnchorRefs.name: pfTblAnchorRefs
pfTblAnchorRefs.description: The number of anchors which reference the table.

pfTblRuleRefs.name: pfTblRuleRefs
pfTblRuleRefs.description: The number of rules which reference the table.

pfTblEvalsMatch.name: pfTblEvalsMatch

pfTblEvalsNoMatch.name: pfTblEvalsNoMatch
pfTblEvalsNoMatch.description: The number of table evaluations that didn't match.

pfTblInPassPkts.name: pfTblInPassPkts
pfTblInPassPkts.description: The number of packets passed in that matched the table.

pfTblInPassBytes.description: The number of bytes passed in that matched the table.

pfTblInBlockPkts.name: pfTblInBlockPkts
pfTblInBlockPkts.description: The number of incoming packets blocked that matched the table.

pfTblInBlockBytes.name: pfTblInBlockBytes
pfTblInBlockBytes.description: The number incoming bytes blocked that matched the table.

pfTblInXPassPkts.name: pfTblInXPassPkts

pfTblInXPassBytes.name: pfTblInXPassBytes

pfTblOutPassPkts.description: The number of packets passed out that matched the table.

pfTblOutPassBytes.description: The number of bytes passed out that matched the table.

pfTblStatsCleared.name: pfTblStatsCleared

pfTblInMatchPkts.name: pfTblInMatchPkts
pfTblInMatchPkts.description: The number of inbound packets that hit a 'match' rule where this particular table was referenced by the rule.

pfTblInMatchBytes.description: The total size in bytes of all inbound packets that hit a 'match' rule where this particular table was referenced by the rule.

pfTblAddrTable.name: pfTblAddrTable
pfTblAddrTable.description: A table containing the addresses/CIDR network blocks from every table on the system.

pfTblAddrEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular table.

pfTblAddrTblIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the table which contains this pfTblAddrNet/pfTblAddrMask pair.

pfTblAddrMask.name: pfTblAddrMask

pfTblAddrCleared.description: The time that's passed since the statistics where last cleared, or since the pfTblAddrNet/pfTblAddrMask pair was loaded into the table, whichever is sooner.
